  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "To set a default font in Gmail, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Gmail**: Go to https://mail.google.com and log in with your Gmail account if you haven't already.\n\n2. **Access Settings**:\n   - Click on the gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f) located in the top right corner of the Gmail interface.\n   - From the dropdown menu, select \"See all settings\" to open the full settings page.\n\n3. **General Tab**: By default, you should land on the \"General\" tab. If not, click on it to access general settings.\n\n4. **Default Text Style**:\n   - Scroll down until you find the \"Default text style\" section.\n   - You\u2019ll see options to change the font type, size, and color.\n\n5. **Customize**:\n   - Click on the drop-down menu for the font and select your preferred font.\n   - You can also adjust the size and color as per your preference.\n\n6. **Save Changes**: After customization, scroll to the bottom of the page and click \"Save Changes\" to apply your new default font settings.\n\nNow, every time you compose a new email in Gmail, it should use your selected default font settings, unless you manually change these in a specific email.",
